programme.desc: Rich, Jim and Scott discuss handgun recoil and how it affects shooters, with tips on gear selection and shooting techniques. Rich and Scott discuss the merits of different targets, and Jim shows how to set up a simple drill with paper plates.(n)

programme.title: Guns & Gear
programme.desc: It's the tactical version of the FN 509, new loads and bullets for Barnes Bullets' VOR-TX and LRX lines, Crimson Trace Laserguards for SIGs, the M1A from Springfield Armory and HEVI-Shot's HEVI-Duty Centerfire ammunition.(n)

programme.title: Bond Arms
programme.desc: Bond Arms, Special Edition. Old Glory Handgun.(n)

programme.title: Gun Stories
programme.desc: A look at the history of the Maxim and Vickers machine guns and how they changed warfare.(n)

programme.title: Guns & Ammo TV
programme.desc: When Craig says this cartridge introduction is the most significant advancement in ammo since paper cartridge cases changed to metallic cases people take notice. Rob Leatham tells us his connection to G&A as a kid.(n)

programme.title: Gallery of Guns
programme.desc: Jeff Sandor gets to channel his inner cowboy with a Henry Lever Action. SIG's Scott Kenneson shows us the P226 Legion, and Travis Tomasie will present the Remington 783 Threaded Barrel. Linda Powell also brings the Mossberg Shockwave to the range.(n)

programme.title: Florida Sportsman Project Dreamboat
programme.desc: We join the experts at TNT Custom Boatworks as they powder coat brand new fuel tanks for the 31' Contender project.(n)

programme.title: Saltwater Experience
programme.desc: A tough day that starts off in a search for bonefish leads Captains Tom Rowland and Rich Tudor down a path of just taking what the day brings.(n)

programme.title: Reel Time With Florida Sportsman
programme.desc: Visting with the Salty Gators, the only saltwater fishing club associated with the University of Florida. Their goal is to expand knowledge on the diverse types of fishing in Florida, while also taking pride in protecting the state's fisheries.(n)

programme.title: Into the Blue
programme.desc: Sneaking away to the Bahamas for a little yellowfin tuna fishing.(n)

programme.title: In-Fisherman
programme.desc: Crazy fast and frantic fishing prevails, as the staff catches arctic grayling on every cast, goes into hand-to-hand combat mode for snag-time channel cats and pitches irresistible tubes to habitat edges for largemouth bass.(n)

programme.title: Major League Bowhunter
programme.desc: Chipper pursues world-class whitetails in a state known for just that, Iowa. Hunting in Iowa has a mythical-like perception for good reason. Chip hunts late October and has numerous encounters with Boone & Crockett bucks.(n)

programme.title: Whitetail Properties
programme.desc: It happens again in south central Kansas. Two giants hit the dirt during the early muzzleloader season. Further proving that Kansas holds and grows great whitetails. The challenge is, as always, the wicked western weather.(n)

programme.title: Brotherhood Outdoors
programme.desc: When union elevator constructor David Morin heads to Kentucky for a trophy buck, he is reminded that nothing is guaranteed in the great outdoors. Back in Minnesota, he hosts an annual walleye tournament for his fellow union brothers.(n)

programme.title: Winchester Deadly Passion
programme.desc: Anytime calling is involved on any hunt it truly turns it up a notch. Melissa and the guys from Convergent Hunting Solutions are calling coyotes, hogs and turkeys down in Texas.(n)

programme.title: The Most Wanted List
programme.desc: Uncle Si and the Sicotics take a break from their Nashville recording studio to join Kristy Lee Cook and guide Lee Orr on a wild hog and coyote hunt.(n)

programme.title: Red Rising
programme.desc: Eric Hale is in Virginia hunting after bucks named Lefty and Johnny Appleseed. Both of these bucks give Eric a run for his money.(n)

programme.title: BuckVentures Outdoors
programme.desc: The crew dives into the big deer history of one of their Oklahoma ranches.(n)

programme.title: McMillan
programme.desc: The season's first hunting clients arrive in camp at McMillan Outfitting, and later, Tom finds a window to hunt for himself in Kansas.(n)

programme.title: Big Boys TV
programme.desc: Kevin and Jada head to Oregon in hopes that Kevin can knock off one more species of his list.(n)

programme.title: In-Fisherman
programme.desc: Crazy fast and frantic fishing prevails, as the staff catches arctic grayling on every cast, goes into hand-to-hand combat mode for snag-time channel cats and pitches irresistible tubes to habitat edges for largemouth bass.(n)

programme.title: Florida Sportsman Project Dreamboat
programme.desc: We join the experts at TNT Custom Boatworks as they powder coat brand new fuel tanks for the 31' Contender project.(n)

programme.title: For Love or Likes
programme.sub-title: Bagging Bucks and Running up the Score
programme.desc: Liberte misses a doe, and then kills a buck. The girls have a trophy taping competition to see who can get the closest to the correct Boone and Crockett score.(n)

programme.title: North American Whitetail Television
programme.desc: Stan Potts bowhunts Illinois and doubles down in Montana with his rifle; Dr. Deer considers whether missing a buck will ruin a hunting spot; and we'll talk real-world archery practice.(n)

programme.title: Hornady's Dark & Dangerous
programme.sub-title: Safari in the Land of Legends
programme.desc: Experience the intense tracking of a wounded cape buffalo in the thick bush of the Zambezi Valley with PH Len Taylor. Also, we begin a safari with veteran PH and elephant expert Buzz Charlton for a legendary valley tusker.(n)

programme.title: Adrenaline
programme.desc: With the rut soon to be underway, hunting over mock scrapes can be deadly. Learn as Kyle Wieter shares his techniques on the best locations for using the Scrape Fix System and then getting the intel to be successful through the use of trail cameras.(n)

programme.title: On The Road With Rock & Aaron
programme.desc: Rock and Steve are in Kentucky looking for a trophy whitetail in velvet.(n)

programme.title: Old School Outdoors
programme.desc: Part 2. After and amazing time at Cheyenne Ridge, Greg Hall and Dennis Branton make a short trip North to Timber Lake, S.D. to chase native bison.(n)

programme.title: Bowed Up
programme.desc: Justin is bowhunting some of the toughest turkeys near his home in south Alabama.(n)

programme.title: All Things Hunting - ATH
programme.desc: Kyle and Cole spend a season in Oklahoma chasing a buck that seems to have no bounds on his home range. The buck named Sticker-Buck is both elusive and visible through most of the season before a full rut encounter gives them a shot.(n)

programme.title: Whitetail Fix
programme.desc: Jose is on a mission in Michigan this year as he shows no mercy or slowing down.(n)
